<div class="pom-container"><div class="pom-container"><p class=""><strong>TUSD Grading During the COVID-19 Closure</strong></p></div></div>
<p class="">In coordinating with the Arizona Department of Education and the State Board of Education, the TUSD Administration team has set the following guidelines for recording grades during the COVID-19 school closure.</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">We will base student's grades on both participation and work performance. These grades will be entered once weekly into Synergy. The grading scale based on participation will be divided into five categories.</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<ul class="">
<li class="">No to minimal participation 0%</li>
<li class="">Low participation 69%</li>
<li class="">Average participation 79%</li>
<li class="">Good participation 89%</li>
<li class="">Excellent participation 100%</li>
</ul>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">Important Information</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<ul class="">
<li class="">Eight weekly grades will be entered into each teachers’ grade books by May 21, teachers will enter work not completed as an absence.</li>
<li class="">Grades K–8 closure period will represent no more than 20% of the final grade</li>
<li class="">Grades 9–12 closure period will represent no more than 40% of the final grade</li>
<li class="">Seniors must complete the state-mandated government/economics class and pass the civics test</li>
<li class="">Late work will receive full credit</li>
</ul>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">A <strong>huge</strong> thanks to all the parents, guardians, grandparents, friends, neighbors who are helping our students navigate this new way of learning. And another <strong>huge</strong> thanks to the teachers and staff at all of the schools for the work they are doing from. We are all in this together!</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">We encourage all students to keep up with their assignments through these uncertain times we are experiencing. If you or your student are feeling overwhelmed and need guidance, please know the TUSD Counseling staff is available. Call the district office or any one of the schools, and we can get you in touch with them.</p>
<div class="pom-container"><p class="">We definitely look forward to the day we can welcome the students back to the classrooms.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p class=""><strong class="">School Closure Due to Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19)</strong></p>
<p class="">Governor Ducey and State Superintendent Hoffman have announced that Arizona schools will remain closed through the end of this school year. <span style="background-color: transparent;" class=""><b>The daily schedule for meal delivery and homework instruction will continue through</b> <b>May 21</b>. Homework Hotlines are open are ready to help at all three schools. We want to congratulate our dedicated staff, parents, and students for their all hard work and cooperation. As we receive any information, we will share it with you.</span></p>
</div>
<p class=""><strong>Daily Breakfast and Lunch During School Closure</strong></p>
<p class="">Beginning on Monday March 30, the meal routes and times have been changed. Both breakfast and lunch are available for pick up on Monday through Friday. Times have have been adjusted to be able to serve more of our students, and there have been some adjustments to pick up sites in Whetstone for the safety of our students. Meals are available for anyone age 0–18, and being a student in in our district is not required. See the current routes below for daily delivery.</p>
<ul class=""><li class=""><a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_246991/site_246992/Documents/Meal-Routes.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">Meal Delivery Routes</a></li></ul>
<p></p>
